LN Gloss: joins two or more noun phrases
joins two or more adjective phrases
joins two or more adverb phrases
joins simultaneous events (The people rejoiced.  And the people celebrated.)
indicates a reason clause, kind of like 'because', but can be used in a separate sentence
it follows that (not strictly logical, like 'therefore')
temporal succession after a significant period of time
and so, marks a summary statement at the end of a discussion
